msgid ""
"The water jet pump has two entry pipes and one exit, and consists, in "
"principle, of two pipes one inside the other. At the water entry a water jet "
"shoots under full pressure out of a nozzle into a slightly larger pipe. The "
"water jet thereby carries away air or fluid from the second entry.\n"
"\t\t<br>\n"
"\t\tThis is caused by the negative pressure in a drifting fluid, and thus it "
"is an application of the hydrodynamic paradox (objects close to drifting "
